args: Luca? Well, this is unusual.\nHave you need of me?
Yeah, I wanted to ask you a couple\nof questions about the other royals.
Yeah. See, I feel like I kind of get Emile,\nbut I don't have a CLUE about the others.
I'd like to know what kind of folks they are\nso I'm ready next time we run into 'em.
I understand your reasons, but to speak\non the royal family so blithely is...
I'd also be interested in filling in some\nof the blanks about my siblings.
You are here as well, Highness?
I figure you'd know more about them than\nmost, Leif, so I'd be happy to hear anything\nyou feel free enough to divulge.
{player_name} knows the score!\nNow c'mon, make with the deets!
Very well, then. To begin with...
Are you all right, Prince Emile?
I am OBVIOUSLY not all right!
Why must I be dragged into the middle of\nthe woods for sword practice like this?!
It is training for field operations.
If you are to lead an army, you must be\nable to react to various battlefield settings.
Wholly unnecessary. Soldiers fight—\nleaders and royalty do not.

There are times when a leader must stand
at the vanguard of battle, Your Highness.
It would be most problematic if you were
unable to do so at such a moment.
And so, I would have you please dedicate\nyourself to your training this day.
Grr! You ALWAYS act so self-important!\nListen here, you—I am PERFECTLY capable\nof doing what needs to be done if I try!
There is nothing I can't do if I just\nput my mind to it and...
Hmm? Leif, look! A suspicious individual!\nI'm going after him!
Prince Emile, wait! It's merely a rabbit!
...Which he already knew when he ran off.

Between being cunning enough to skive off
his daily training and the strength of his
competitive spirit, he may yet make a
fine commander. However...
We offer our most humble thanks for\nyour service in slaying those fiends!
Three cheers for Prince Valyx!\nHip hip, hooraaaaaaaaa...?
Er, Prince Valyx? Is something amiss?
Prince Valyx, you must reply to the\ncitizenry when they call out to you.\nYour silence makes them most anxious.
Hmm, yes. ...Rest easy, good people!\nThe fiends have been wiped out;\nyou need worry no more this day!
Three cheers for Prince Valyx!\nHip hip, hooray! Hip hip, hooray!
I grow weary of this buffoonery, Leif.\nIt was you who proposed the strategy\nthat wiped out the fiends, not I.
I assure you, Highness, it is not—
I will not stand here and accept praise\nthat belongs to another like a common\nnote-cribber in a class.
I assume you would have ME stand\nbefore the people in that case?
I would not; I know it is my duty as a\nroyal to ease the hearts of the people.
To be a royal is to put to rest my own\nemotions if doing so will help preserve\nthe order of the kingdom.
I admire the strength of your responsibility.\nHowever, I believe it is also good to\nprioritize your own emotions on occasion.
Tsk! You couldn't BE more awkward, Leif.\nDo try to relax a little, mmm?
With all due respect, Princess Chelle,\nis there not a more accomplished\npartner with whom to practice dancing?
I worry that my inexperience with this\nmanner of thing will only result in me\nteaching you poor habits.
This is not practice for me, but for YOU.

Because when there's a party and I choose 
you to be my dance partner, it would be
most shameful if you stumbled about the
floor like a common barnyard animal.
Perhaps you should NOT select me,\nin that case?
I am free to choose whomever I wish.\nNow then! We continue.
You're quite diligent, after all—I'm certain\nyou'll strive to improve so you don't\nembarrass me! Eee hee!
You are a complicated one, Highness.
...Prince Phares, I have brought\nthe books you requested.
Thank you, Leif—and forgive me for having\nyou do the work of a serving boy.
I have been absorbed in my research and\nnot shown my face to those in the castle,\nso I suspect they are all quite exasperated.
Not at all, Your Highness. Your research\nis of great use to peace in the realm.
You even ended up producing a medicine\nthat cured an illness once thought to be\nincurable. Everyone is most grateful.
Though I've yet to produce a medicine\nthat can cure my own condition.
Think nothing of it. After all, I view my\nhaving been afflicted with this illness\nas a twist of good fortune.
Have you ever given thought to what\nthe dragon's blood IS, Leif?
Noble blood that ought be respected,\nas well as a cornerstone of our kingdom.
Yes, yes. All that and more. And yet,\nthat same noble blood has made\nmy body like... Well, like this.
I believe a secret is hidden within the\ndragon's blood, and I wonder if my body\nmight be most intimately related to it.

And I admit no small amount of eagerness
to seeing what might become of our
kingdom should the secret at its
foundation be exposed...
(Prince Phares is possessed of a\nmost magnificent intellect.)
(Though I pray he never walks an\nerrant path for the sake of it...)
...Those are but a few of the things\nI recall about your siblings.
Hot diggity dog! I mean, I kinda figured it\nalready, but those siblings of yours...
Well, they sure do have some unique\npersonalities.
Heh. Yeah, I guess I'm rather\nunremarkable, all in all...
You think some unremarkable schmo could\nmake pacts with a buncha dragons?!\n...C'mon, Leif! Back me up here!
Luca is correct, Your Highness. You have\njust as much individuality as your siblings.
Thank you both. But that reminds me,\nI still had some things I wanted to\ndiscuss about Leonidas.
Ugh. He's the biggest handful of the bunch!
Prince Leonidas has excelled in\nboth the martial and literary arts\nsince a young age.
We diligently studied both together as we\nhoned our skills with a blade.
Together? Wait, I thought you were the\nguy what taught all the royals how to\nwave a poker around.
With Prince Leonidas, it's probably fairer\nto say we were classmates as opposed\nto teacher and pupil.
Well, I'll be a monkey's uncle.
He was a force of nature who shocked us\nall by the ease with which he dispatched\nknights many times his years.
So he's been strong since he was a kid?
I heard he absolutely couldn't\ntolerate losing.
That would explain how he turned into\na guy that's like a burning inferno.
Yes, you could call him that.\nPrince Leonidas is an exceptionally\nstrong and fearsome man.
(I saw that tendency in him long ago,\nbut now...)
Suppose I were to be the one standing\nin the way of the peace you espouse.\nWould you put me to the sword?
(I pray his fire does not blaze so hot that it\nburns this world to ash...)
